The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, June 07, 2004 				 Mulayam son tastes Dalit ire
				 	 Akhilesh: Attacked																								Kannauj, June 6 (PTI): Uttar Pradesh chief minister Mulayam Singh Yadavs son Akhilesh, the local MP, was attacked following the recovery of the bodies of two Dalit children who were abducted on Friday near Naurachandpur village, police said.																								Their bodies were recovered last evening, leading to tension in the area, the police said. Villagers pelted stones at the police party that went to take the bodies for post-mortem.																								Akhileshs vehicle also came under attack. He was rescued uninjured by security guards and police after two hours, the police said. His vehicle was partially damaged.																								Villagers also blocked traffic on GT Road and damaged several vehicles. The situation was brought under control after additional forces reached the spot.																								The MP announced a compensation of Rs 50,000 to the next of the kin of the deceased from his MP fund while the district administration announced a relief of Rs 10,000 to the families of the deceased.Agitation threat																								The BJP, the main Opposition party in Uttar Pradesh, and the Congress that is supporting the Mulayam Singh Yadav government from outside on Sunday threatened to launch separate agitations against alleged failure of law and order in the state.																								Opposition leader Lalji Tandon claimed that the state government had failed on all fronts and the crimegraph had shot up drastically over the last few months. People were not feeling safe, he said. State Congress president Jagdambika Pal has also threatened to launch a satyagraha to protest alleged deterioration in law and order and persecution of party workers. 
